title: Database
text: Although you will use the database or source data, it is typically not the first place you want to start.

title: Existing Reports
text: Existing reports can help you with your baseline understanding of the project you are trying to tackle

title: Technical Documentation
text: Technical documentation is handy and valuable, but to get the most from the documentation, it's helpful to understand more about something else being used at an organization and not start with documentation.

title: Queries
text: As an analyst you will be writing queries, but at the outset of any project, looking at the queries that have been developed already can give you a faster start. Created queries can be found in existing reports.
